summary: so i see a lot of stuff about alternate lyrics that we know now from the making of a song vids but no one said anything about...
body:
so i see a lot of stuff about alternate lyrics that we know now from the making of a song vids but no one said anything about the original lyric for the bridge of idsb: they got their pitchforks outside

idk why but that struck something in me, and then i remembered the imagery in ciwyw of shutting yourself up inside a house
all my flowers grew back as thorns, windows boarded up after the storm
the thorns protect her, kinda like sleeping beauty, and the boarded up windows shut out the world

so this alternate lyric from idsb kinda lends itself to this imagery, of taylor huddled up in her house with people gathering outside with pitchforks so she had to go to extreme measures to block them out

tags: look what you made me do
summary: Look what you made us do, these sisters are repping the New & Old Taylor just for YOU @taylorswift, bahaha we can’t even say it...
caption:
Look what you made us do, these sisters are repping the New & Old Taylor just for YOU @taylorswift, bahaha we can’t even say it with a straight face 😆 Hey Taylor!! My name’s Lexi and this is my little sister, MaryAnn. We’re from Chicago and even though there are 12 years between us, we’re the best concert buddies you will ever find. There’s absolutely no one I would rather dance, sing and scream with at a show.  

We saw you for the first time three years ago and in Chicago this year for the reputation tour, and we are counting down the days until we see you again. Thank you for being a part of our friendship, you’ve made these two sisters very, very happy :)

Catch us in our coordinating costumes on September 15th in Indianapolis!! We’ll be in Sec K, Row 2, seats 29-30. See you & @taylornation soon!! We’re so excited to shake, shake, shake one more time 💋 #reputationStadiumTour #repTourIndy @reputationcostumes
